<img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-70418" src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Adamawa-assembly-720x479.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="479" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Adamawa-assembly-720x479.jpg 720w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Adamawa-assembly-150x100.jpg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Adamawa-assembly-420x279.jpg 420w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Adamawa-assembly.jpg 744w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /> Adamawa House of Assembly on Wednesday granted approval to Gov. Muhammadu Bindowâ€™s request to source for N5 billion loan from UBA Plc to pay salary arrears of the local government workers. The House unanimously approved the request with a resolution that the House would ensure strict supervision to ensure judicious utilisation of the loan. However, the House Deputy Speaker, Emmanuel Tsamdu (APC-Madagali), Majority Leader, Hassan Barguma (APC-Hong), Deputy Leader, Abubakar Isa (APC-Shellenge) and Deputy Chief Whip, Abdullahi Yapak (APC-Verre) have lamented the problem of salary payment in local government. They lawmakers stressed the need for the state government to take concrete steps to ensure lasting solution to the problem. The House at the plenary, presided over by the Speaker, Kabiru Mijinyawa, also confirmed the appointment of Zaphaniya Bakari and Gabriel Zenas as Administrators of Gengle and Tola Development Areas.. The House also received a letter from the governor and read to it, requesting confirmation of nominees for appointment as chairman and members of the State Fiscal Responsibility Commission. The nominees are: Dahiru Adamu as chairman while Husseini Adamu, Baba Galadima and Solome Shamaki are to serve as members. The nominees have been directed by the speaker, who read the letter, to appear before the House Standing Committee on Public Service for screening. The speaker said the nominees would be communicated to as to when they would appear before the committee. (NAN) Hinatufe Henry Solomon is a graduate of Computer Science, specialist in ICT Support Services. Henry is also proficient in use of most online journalism tools and Social media management. He currently serve as Information Technology Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network.